England win by eight wickets! With 101 balls to spare
Pre-Game Insights: England skittled Oman for 47 as Adil Rashid claimed four wickets then chased down their target with 101 balls to spare
The weather was good for the match
England have never successfully defended a World Cup in cricket, football or rugby
England’s hopes of bashing 109 in ten overs against Scotland were washed away by the Bridgetown rain
England’s bowlers were flayed by the Scottish openers, then marmalised by the Aussie ones
England now face what are on paper their two easiest assignments, against Oman and Namibia
Oman have even fewer points than England (none), but only because they lost to Namibia in a Super Over
Both games are at the Viv Richards Stadium in Antigua and, weather permitting, England should win them by a street
Post-Match Reflections: We had a point to prove, says Wood
Miscellaneous Highlights: England kickstarted their T20 World Cup campaign with an eight-wicket victory over Oman at North Sound
